# OPS/_llm/200 — react to a finished exchange.
#
# After the upstream stream ends, the gateway fires a second envelope
# into this same stack with @llm.phase == "completed" — the client
# never waits on it. Available here:
#   @llm.completion.{status,duration_ms,bytes_in,bytes_out,stream,
#                    client_disconnected}
#   @llm.completion.{requested_model,effective_request_model,
#                    response_model}          — explicit provenance
#   @llm.completion.usage.{input_tokens,output_tokens,
#                          cache_read_input_tokens,
#                          cache_creation_input_tokens}  — presence-
#                    gated: absent means "not captured", never zero
#   @llm.completion.stop_reason
#   @llm.context_result — the gateway's ground truth of context
#                    injection: per-item {source,title,sha256,bytes,
#                    est_tokens,status} plus the synthetic guard row.
#                    sha256, never content.
# Ready for billing counters, audit trails, kv/incr budgets. This demo
# just stamps a marker so the completion run is visible in the trace.
WHEN @src == "llm" && @llm.phase == "completed"
  EMIT .audit = "llm request completed"
